# Prompt Template: Testing (Unit Tests)

**Version**: v1.0  
**Purpose**: Generate unit test cases with happy path, edge cases, and error handling  
**Framework**: xUnit (C#), Jasmine (TypeScript), pytest (Python)  
**Complexity**: Medium-High

---

## Template Parameters

Replace placeholders with your values:

- `{PROJECT_CONTEXT}` — E.g., "Election Voting backend with clean architecture"
- `{FILE_PATH}` — E.g., "backend/ElectionVoting.Application/Services/EmployeeService.cs"
- `{CLASS_NAME}` — E.g., "EmployeeService"
- `{LANGUAGE}` — E.g., "C#" or "TypeScript"
- `{TEST_FRAMEWORK}` — E.g., "xUnit", "Jasmine", "NUnit"
- `{METHODS_TO_TEST}` — List of methods needing tests
- `{COVERAGE_GOAL}` — E.g., "95%"
- `{EDGE_CASES}` — Special cases to test
- `{STANDARDS_FILE}` — E.g., ".instructions-backend.md"

---

## Prompt Template

```
Context & Requirements
======================

Project: {PROJECT_CONTEXT}
Class/Component: {CLASS_NAME}
File: {FILE_PATH}
Language: {LANGUAGE}
Test Framework: {TEST_FRAMEWORK}
Standards Reference: {STANDARDS_FILE}
Target Coverage: {COVERAGE_GOAL}

Methods to Test
===============

Test these methods/functions:
{METHODS_TO_TEST}

Test Scenarios
==============

For each method, create test cases for:

1. **Happy Path** (normal, expected input)
   - Valid input that should succeed
   - Expected output/return value
   - State changes verified

2. **Edge Cases** (boundary conditions)
   - Empty inputs
   - Null values
   - Maximum/minimum values
   - First/last items in collection
   {EDGE_CASES}

3. **Error Cases** (invalid input, exceptions)
   - Invalid parameters
   - Business rule violations
   - Service failures (dependency throwsexception)
   - Expected exceptions thrown correctly

4. **Integration Points**
   - Dependencies mocked appropriately
   - Mock verification (called correct number of times)
   - Exception handling from dependencies

Test Structure
==============

For each test case, provide:

**Test Name**: Descriptive name following: MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult
- Example: CreateEmployee_WithValidEmail_ReturnsEmployeeId

**Arrange** (Setup)
- Create test data
- Setup mocks/dependencies
- Configure state

**Act** (Execute)
- Call method under test
- Pass test data

**Assert** (Verify)
- Verify return value
- Verify state changes
- Verify mock calls

Code Quality
============

Follow {STANDARDS_FILE} patterns:
- [ ] Use async/await for async methods
- [ ] Proper exception handling
- [ ] Arrange-Act-Assert structure
- [ ] Descriptive test names
- [ ] One assertion concept per test
- [ ] No test interdependencies
- [ ] Proper dispose/cleanup
- [ ] Mock external dependencies

Output Format
==============

Generate test class with:

```
[TestClass / describe()]
public class {CLASS_NAME}Tests / describe('{CLASS_NAME}')
{
    // Setup/fixtures
    
    // Test 1: Happy path
    [TestMethod / it()]
    public async Task MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult_Async()
    {
        // Arrange
        // Act
        // Assert
    }
    
    // Test 2-N: Edge/error cases
    // ... more tests
}
```

Coverage Analysis
=================

After generating tests, verify:
- [ ] All methods have happy path tests
- [ ] All parameters tested (null, empty, invalid)
- [ ] All return types tested (success, null, empty)
- [ ] All exceptions tested
- [ ] All branches tested (if/else)
- [ ] Coverage goal achieved ({COVERAGE_GOAL})

Test Data Requirements
=====================

Identify needed test data:
- Valid/invalid examples for each parameter
- Fixture data (reusable test objects)
- Mock responses for dependencies
- Edge case values

Estimate Effort
===============

How long should testing take:
- Happy path tests: X minutes
- Edge case tests: Y minutes
- Error case tests: Z minutes
- Total: (X + Y + Z) minutes
```

